Dolce&Gabbana stay true to their heritage with the #DGFW23 Men’s Fashion Show “Essenza”. A pure vision of the brand’s traditions dresses the man with elegance, precision and sensuality. 
 
The emotion of the new black volcanic hues, the tailored cut, the exceptional Italian craftsmanship of #DGFattoAMano in the precious embroideries and Sicilian inspiration.  A collection that narrates the true essence of #DolceGabbana.

@kimkardashian is the contemporary diva and the ultimate muse. Her confidence, independence and sensuality, along with her love for legendary #DolceGabbana pieces, inspired Domenico Dolce and Stefano Gabbana to revisit the 90s and 00s archives. The result is the #DGSS23 Collection curated by Kim in person, a magical alchemy between the designers’ creativity and her inclusive vision of beauty. 
 
Discover the collection at the link in bio.

Music: The Stereotypes and 9am 
 
#CiaoKim #DGDNA

“Cu chello mare argiènto, cu chello cielo dipinto, cu chello sole bianco” 
 
With visuals by @juergentellerstudio and styling by @poppykain, the new #DGFW22 campaign tells the story of a mystic fascination with Naples to the notes of the song “Napule Canta E More” performed by Donatella Viggiano. 
 
 
The latest #DolceGabbana Collection, with its daringly provocative and futuristic looks, moves through the city of heart and instinct. 
 
Discover more at the link in bio. 
 
“Napule Canta E More” (F. Mengucci / S. Nicolò / G. Mambelli) 
Courtesy of Sugarmusic S.p.A.

Siracusa 2022: Dolce&Gabbana Alta Sartoria Fashion Show in Marzamemi. 

The #DGAltaSartoria Collection tells a story of eternal life. Bold structures handmade from mythological inspirations frame the male forms, enhancing the anatomy as if they were forged on the bodies themselves. 

#DGLovesSicily #DGFattoAMano #MadeInItaly #DolceGabbana

The #DGAltaModa Collection is history and tale. Profound representations of Sicily and its people, the unique pieces evoke exquisite beauty, traditions and timeless Italian craftsmanship. 
  
Crochet dress with tulle base embroidered by hand with nets, flowers, scalloped hems, spirals and leaves to reproduce the absolutely unique and classic Sicilian lace. 
  
Relive the Alta Moda show and discover more at the link in bio. 
#DGLovesSicily #DGFattoAMano #MadeInItaly #DolceGabbana

The #DGAltaModa event is history and tale. Profound representations of Sicily and its people, the unique pieces of the Collection touch the mythical ground of the oldest heart of the city, evoking exquisite beauty, traditions and timeless Italian craftsmanship.

#DGLovesSicily #DGFattoAMano #MadeInItaly #DolceGabbana

Returning to where everything began. Sicily is an infinite universe of culture, styles and traditions that have always animated creativity. 
  
Magical at any time of day or night, with its rounded forms and the unrivalled richness of its ornaments, the millenary history and incomparable beauty of Siracusa opens its most ancient heart to #DolceGabbana and the exquisite art of #DGAltaModa. 
  
Follow the events on Instagram from the 8th of July. 
#DGLovesSicily #DGFattoAMano #MadeInItaly

Repost from @lalarudge 
 
In the occasion of her Bal Masqué wedding party, Lala Trussardi Rudge Khouri wore a custom-made gown created by Domenico Dolce and Stefano Gabbana. 
 
The #DolceGabbana ball gown features a corset construction in extra-fine tulle, encrusted with Chantilly lace on the bustier and on the hem. Boning, neckline, straps and belt are made of gold crystal mesh. 
 
The look was completed with a cape, gloves, and a headpiece, which was later changed for a crown, and with a #DGAltaGioielleria necklace in yellow beryl filigree and twisted gold wire. 
 
Video by @christybarley 
 
#DGCelebs

The story of Domenico Dolce and Stefano Gabbana is one steeped in synergy and creativity. The two designers' paths first crossed over the phone in 1980, and four years later, with a limited budget and a shared passion to follow their dreams, they created what was destined to become an example of Italian excellence around the world. 
 
Behind the scenes of “The Strength of Connections”, the new institutional campaign of @timofficial by Oscar-winning director Giuseppe Tornatore with the glorious soundtrack of Ennio Morricone. A project by #TIM and #DolceGabbana that tells the story of the connection between Stefano Gabbana and Domenico Dolce and shows how connection helps us achieve our most ambitious projects. 
 
#LaForzaDelleConnessioni

latestIgtvVideos.title: La Forza Delle Connessioni
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
The story of Domenico Dolce and Stefano Gabbana is one steeped in synergy and creativity. The two designers' paths first crossed over the phone in 1980, and four years later, with a limited budget and a shared passion to follow their dreams, they created what was destined to become an example of Italian excellence around the world. 
 
A young Domenico Dolce and Stefano Gabbana who meet, connect and realise their dreams. This is the story of “The Strength of Connections”, the new institutional campaign of @timofficial by Academy Award-winning director Giuseppe Tornatore accompanied by the notes of an unpublished piece by Academy Award-winning composer Ennio Morricone. 
 
The partnership between TIM and #DolceGabbana underlines the importance of connection that becomes a human relationship, helping us get closer, overcome distances and find the strength and motivation to achieve our most ambitious projects. 
 
#LaForzaDelleConnessioni

Passion. Nostalgia. Memories. Dreams. Magic. Feelings blend with space. Space embraces emotions. A love letter read through objects, sensations and moving bodies, a creative and surprising unison in the new @dolcegabbana_casa campaign shot by photographer duo @mertalas and @macpiggott.

On the occasion of her most special day, @laurensanchezbezos wore a one-of-a-kind #DGAltaModa wedding dress that caught the eye in @voguemagazine. Crafted from the finest Italian lace, the gown is adorned with a refined floral motif, and each element is hand-appliqued to create a seamless visual flow and make all structural cuts invisible. The 180 silk chiffon-covered hand-finished buttons gently cascade down the front.

#DolceGabbana #DGFattoAMano
